node.title: The Game Awards Returns With Glitz and an Industry Asserting Its Muscle
node.description: On Thursday night, the video game industry held its big awards event, which is quickly becoming as important — and as long — as certain other entertainment occasions.

node.title: Diplomats Warn Russia of ‘Massive Consequences’ if It Invades Ukraine
node.description: The foreign ministers for the Group of 7 urged Russia to pull back from the tense border standoff. It has massed as many as 100,000 troops on Ukraine’s eastern, northern and southern frontiers.

node.title: Talking Tech With "Your Korean Dad" Creator Nick Cho
node.description: TikTok star Nick Cho of "Your Korean Dad" fame talks a bit of tech and gives some recommendations around content creation and travel.

node.title: Trump Blames 'Smart and Sharp' Obama for Creating 'Tremendous Division' in America
node.description: Even as he criticized his predecessor, Trump said that he "liked" Obama.

node.title: Rep. Ritchie Torres on "that triumph of hope"
node.description: The 15th Congressional District in New York's South Bronx is the poorest in the country, and for the young Democrat – the first Afro-Latino gay Congressman – fighting to support the social safety net isn't partisan; it's personal.

node.title: Jill Biden on being first lady
node.description: "Sunday Morning" visits Camp David for a rare interview with Dr. Biden, who talks about promoting the administration's work; and joins the Bidens at the White House Christmas tree to reflect on their life together.

node.title: Democrats Are Solidly Behind Biden. There’s No Consensus About a Plan B.
node.description: Leaders with White House aspirations all say they’ll support the president for another term. But there is no shortage of chatter about the options if he continues to falter.

node.title: New Caledonia Says ‘Non’ to Independence
node.description: The vote on the Pacific island territory comes as France’s president, Emmanuel Macron, has made shoring up the country’s international profile a priority and sees its military in the region as a bulwark against China.

node.title: Tiger Who Ate Seven Pets in Local Village Released Back Into the Wild
node.description: Given a shortage of boars, a hungry tiger targeted local dogs before if was trapped and released back into the wild.

node.title: The James Webb Space Telescope: Looking back towards the beginning of time
node.description: 100 times more powerful than Hubble, it's the most ambitious, complex space observatory ever built, and its launch next week will usher in a new era in our understanding of the origin and evolution of the cosmos.

node.title: Maggie Gyllenhaal in the director's chair
node.description: The Oscar-nominated actress (and movie buff) talks about her first feature as director: a psychological thriller, "The Lost Daughter," based on the Elena Ferrante novel, that tells both uncomfortable and liberating truths regarding motherhood.

node.title: Answering letters to Santa Claus
node.description: For more than 90 years, letters from across the globe have found their way to the post office in Santa Claus, Indiana, where teams of elves keep up with the mail.

node.title: Saturday Night Live Skit Mocks 'Disgraced' Brothers Chris Cuomo, Andrew Cuomo
node.description: SNL's cold open joked about why former New York Governor Andrew Cuomo and ex-CNN host Chris Cuomo lost their jobs.

node.title: Fran Lebowitz speaks her mind
node.description: Most writers write; Fran Lebowitz talks. The opinionated essayist and raconteur discusses the reaction of her parents to her outspoken manner; why she still smokes; and her thoughts on gay marriage.

node.title: RFK's children speak out on Sirhan Sirhan
node.description: After more than five decades, California's parole board has recommended that Sen. Robert F. Kennedy's assassin, now 77, be granted parole. Chris and Kerry Kennedy oppose giving their father's killer his freedom.

node.title: ‘Sesame Street’ Was Always Political
node.description: The beloved children’s show has been a recurrent culture-war target, but a documentary on HBO shows how social purpose was built into it.

node.title: New Caledonia votes 'no' to independence for third time
node.description: With all ballots counted, 96.49 per cent were against independence, while only 3.51 per cent were in favour, from a turn-out of 43.90 per cent, according to New Caledonia's high commission.

node.title: Abu Dhabi Grand Prix: How to Watch
node.description: Lewis Hamilton and Max Verstappen go into the Formula 1 season finale tied for the championship.

node.title: Author of Interview with the Vampire, Anne Rice, dies aged 80
node.description: Ms Rice, whose books sold more than 150 million copies, died due to complications from a stroke, her son Christopher Rice announced on Facebook and Twitter.

node.title: Live Updates: Search continues for victims of deadly tornadoes
node.description: "I pray that there will be another rescue. I pray that there will be another one or two," Kentucky Governor Andy Beshear said.

node.title: Electric Cooler Dometic CFX3 35 Is Like a Portable Fridge for Trips and Parties
node.description: A powered cooler like the CFX3 35 from Dometic can keep food or drinks cold at a set temperature without the need for ice.

node.title: Watch Spanish Police Chase Drug Dealers in Speedboat as They Throw Cannabis Overboard
node.description: The Civil Guard has arrested six people and seized 2.5 tons of hashish in Ayamonte, Huelva in Spain.

node.title: Gavin Newsom Turns Texas Abortion Law Ruling on Guns
node.description: "If states can now shield their laws...then California will use that authority to protect people's lives," Newsom said.

node.title: Why Taking a Cold Shower After Workouts Boosts Recovery and Muscle Repair
node.description: If you're not feeling brave enough to throw yourself into an ice bath, try a cold shower instead to reap many of the same benefits.

node.title: F1's crazy season comes to an end with one race for the championship
node.description: Will Lewis Hamilton stand alone as the most successful Formula 1 driver in history or can Max Verstappen dethrone the Mercedes king? Follow live.

node.title: At 64, Finding His Own Community — And His Own Pace — Through Running
node.description: Training for a race can be all about getting to the finish line. But for many runners, it’s about much more.

node.title: Israel Prime Minister Naftali Bennett announces historic visit to UAE as fears over Iran grow
node.description: Mr Bennett is the first Israeli leader to visit the UAE while in office, and follows a visit by the UAE's national security adviser Sheikh Tahnoon bin Zayed Al Nahyan to Tehran.

node.title: Anne Rice, Who Spun Gothic Tales of Vampires and Ghouls, Dies at 80
node.description: She wrote more than 30 Gothic novels, including the best seller “Interview With the Vampire,” published in 1976 and later turned into a hit movie starring Tom Cruise and Brad Pitt.

node.title: Israeli Leader Is to Meet Emirati Prince, Showcasing Deepening Ties
node.description: Prime Minister Naftali Bennett will travel to Abu Dhabi on Sunday — the first such visit by an Israeli leader.

node.title: Donald Trump and Bill O'Reilly's Tour Begins With Empty Seats in Florida—Report
node.description: Empty seats were seen at the FLA Live Arena in Sunrise, Florida, for the first stop of Trump and O'Reilly's "History Tour."
